                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout style="other">The stone is classified as an ogham stone on a 1971 map of Britain in the Dark Ages by the Ordnance Survey but there is no other mention of the presence of ogham on the stone. The stone is inscribed with a roman-letter inscription in four vertical lines reading downwards. The inscription faced south.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>There is no evidence to indicate how the ogham inscription might have been carved, so the execution technique remains <rs type="execution" key="other">unknown</rs>. The execution of Latin inscription is described as <q>deeply cut (or recut?)</q> but is otherwise undetermined (Redknap and Lewis 2007, 407).
                            </handNote>
